# 0.7.2 PR-3 — empirical performance data (AC-013 / AC-013b / AC-019)

**Status:** measurement record (local). Feeds the tiered budget in
`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md` and the PR-3 closure
artifact `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-3-output.json`.

This file is the authoritative empirical record for the 0.7.2 PR-3 latency /
recall measurement gate. Every row keeps its full settings (N, dim, K,
samples, seed time, env knobs, host) so a future reader can reproduce or
re-derive without re-running.

## Why these were run locally (not canonical CI)

HITL 2026-05-31/06-01: the real default-embedder (bge-small) + real-corpus
measurement at N=1M is infeasible on the 4-core canonical runner — seeding
1M docs through the serialized candle projection path is ~166 h at the
PR-9-measured **1.67 docs/s** vs a 240-min workflow timeout. So the heavy
measurement is a **local once-per-release exercise**; CI carries only a fast
"is the read path broken?" guard (`perf_gates::ac_013_vector_read_path_smoke`).
See `dev/notes/ac013-ac019-canonical-scale-policy.md` and
`dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-3-output.json`.

## Common configuration (unless a row says otherwise)

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Engine read path | two-phase bit-KNN (sign-bit Hamming candidates) + f32 rerank, then canonical-body fetch + FTS5 MATCH + soft-fallback probe (4 SQL statements / `search()` call) |
| `TOP_K_BIT_CANDIDATES` (K) | **192** (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3012`; locked) |
| Production search `LIMIT` | 10 |
| Samples per percentile | 1000 (`PERF_SAMPLES`); warmup pass discarded |
| Percentile method | `percentile_ceil` (sorted, ceil index) |
| Build | `cargo test --release -p fathomdb-engine --test perf_gates` |
| Perf env knobs | **none** (no `FATHOMDB_PERF_*`, no pcache2, no `page_size=8192`, no reader/writer PRAGMAs). Plain default engine. |
| Mean-centering | synthetic fixture: OFF (VaryingEmbedder identity does not request it). Real bge: ON, pinned at first 256 docs (production behaviour). |
| Host | AMD Ryzen Threadripper PRO 5945WX (12c/24t), Linux 6.17 x86_64, rustc 1.95.0 |
| Repo HEAD | `25ab3ee` (+ PR-3 working-tree test edits: env-tunable dim & drain) |
| Date | 2026-06-01 (UTC) |

**Dimension note.** The synthetic `VaryingEmbedder` fixture defaults to
`RETRIEVAL_VECTOR_DIM=768` (legacy ADR-0.6.0 assumption). The **shipped**
default embedder `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` is **dim 384**
(`fathomdb-embedder/src/candle_bge.rs:48`). Bit-KNN scan + f32 rerank cost
scales ~linearly with dim, so 768-d synthetic over-states production-faithful
latency. Rows are tagged with the dim actually measured. The PR-3 working tree
adds env knobs `AC013_VECTOR_DIM` (default 768) and `AC013_DRAIN_TIMEOUT_MS`
(default 1_800_000) so the dimension and seed-drain budget are tunable for the
local canonical exercise without touching committed defaults.

## AC-013 — vector-retrieval latency (single-reader)

`perf_gates::ac_013_vector_retrieval_latency`. Synthetic fixture = dense
isotropic `VaryingEmbedder` over the deterministic Zipfian corpus
(`seed_ac013_corpus`). Real fixture = `CandleBgeEmbedder` over
`data/corpus-data/raw/*.jsonl` (from `eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs`).

| fixture | embedder | dim | N | K | samples | seed_ms | p50 ms | p99 ms | budget (p50/p99) | verdict | source / log |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| synthetic | VaryingEmbedder (isotropic) | 384 | 10,000 | 192 | 1000 | 2,183 | **15** | **17** | 80 / 300 | PASS | `0.7.2-PR-3-local-10k.log` |
| synthetic | VaryingEmbedder (isotropic) | 768 | 10,000 | 192 | 1000 | 2,267 | **22** | **27** | 80 / 300 | PASS | `0.7.2-PR-3-local-10k.log` |
| **real** | **bge-small-en-v1.5** | **384** | **7,667** | 192 | 1000 | — | **36** | **49** | 80 / 300 | **PASS** | `0.7.1-EU-7-measurements.json` (PR-2c re-measure) |
| real | bge-small-en-v1.5 | 384 | 7,667 | 192 | 1000 | — | 25 | 40 | 80 / 300 | PASS | `0.7.1-EU-7-output.json` (original EU-7) |
| real | bge-small-en-v1.5 | 384 | 1,000 | 192 | 1000 | — | 16 | 30 | 80 / 300 | PASS | `0.7.1-EU-7-output.json` |
| synthetic | VaryingEmbedder (isotropic) | 384 | 100,000 | 192 | 1000 | 182,257 | **147** | **198** | 80 / 300 | p50 MISS (1.8×) | `0.7.2-PR-3-local-384-100k.log` |
| synthetic | VaryingEmbedder (isotropic) | 768 | 100,000 | 192 | 1000 | 180,312 | **190** | **244** | 80 / 300 | p50 MISS (2.4×) | `0.7.2-PR-3-local-100k.log` |
| synthetic | VaryingEmbedder (isotropic) | 384 | 1,000,000 | 192 | 1000 | — | **n/a** | **n/a** | 80 / 300 | seed drain did not reach idle in **3 h** (`Err(Scheduler)`) | `0.7.2-PR-3-local-384-1m.log` |
| synthetic | VaryingEmbedder (isotropic) | 768 | 1,000,000 | 192 | 1000 | — | n/a | n/a | 80 / 300 | seed drain did not reach idle in 30 min (`Err(Scheduler)`) | `0.7.2-PR-3-local-canonical.log` |
| synthetic (0.7.0 W4.1, **pre-bit-quant** f32 brute) | VaryingEmbedder | 768 | 1,000,000 | n/a | 1000 | — | 2,048 | 2,327 | (RED that motivated bit-quant) | historical | `0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json` |

### Scaling — latency is ~O(N) (no ANN index on vec0)

The vec0 bit-KNN is a per-query **linear** scan over all N rows (no HNSW/IVF
index; see `dev/notes/ac013-ac019-canonical-scale-policy.md` "long-term
follow-up"). The measured synthetic points confirm near-linear growth:

| dim | N=10K p50 | N=100K p50 | ratio (10×N) | implied 1M p50 (linear) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 384 (prod) | 15 ms | 147 ms | 9.8× | ~1,470 ms |
| 768 | 22 ms | 190 ms | 8.6× | ~1,900 ms |

So at the shipped 384-d, p50 is ~**O(N)** with coefficient ≈ **1.5 ms per
1,000 docs** plus a small fixed per-query overhead (the FTS MATCH + soft-
fallback probe + parse run on every `search()` regardless of N). The 10k
binding-tier number is **15 ms (synthetic 384-d) / 36 ms (real bge, N=7667
≈ 10k)**; linear scaling sets the 100k tier near 147 ms and the 1M tier near
1.5 s — i.e. the 80 ms p50 budget is **not** met above ~50k without an ANN
index. This is the data behind the tiered ADR decision (10k binding for
0.x/1.x; 100k/1M tracked targets for post-1.0, pre-2.1 ANN work).

### Seed-cost finding (why 1M did not complete locally)

Seeding is **super-linear** on the default per-row projection path:
N=100K drained in ~182 s (~550 docs/s), but N=1M did **not** drain in 3 h
(`wait_for_idle` timeout → `Err(Scheduler)`; **not** a wedge — see
`Engine::drain` at `lib.rs:1995`). vec0 b-tree insertion + sign-bit quantize
+ WAL growth cost rises with table size. 0.7.0 obtained its 1M number only via
the W4.1 perf-knob seed path (pcache2 + `page_size=8192`), which the plain
`cargo test` path here does not enable. The 1M tier is therefore recorded from
the 0.7.0 W4.1 historical anchor + the O(N) extrapolation above, not a fresh
local run.

## AC-013b — recall@10 vs f32 ground truth

| fixture | embedder | dim | N | K | queries | recall@10 | 95% CI | floor | verdict | source |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **real (anchor)** | **bge-small-en-v1.5 + mean-center** | **384** | **7,667** | 192 | 100 | **0.937** | 0.913–0.957 (σ=0.0116) | 0.90 | **PASS** | `0.7.1-EU-7-measurements.json` (PR-2c re-measure; exclude-before + dedup GT) |
| real | bge-small-en-v1.5 + mean-center | 384 | 7,667 | 192 | 100 | 0.828 | 0.796–0.858 (σ=0.0165) | 0.90 | (superseded artifact) | `0.7.1-EU-7-output.json` (original; exclude-after + set-GT) |
| real | bge-small-en-v1.5 + mean-center | 384 | 1,000 | 192 | 100 | 0.831 | 0.803–0.856 | 0.90 | (superseded artifact) | `0.7.1-EU-7-output.json` |
| synthetic (isotropic noise floor, reference) | VaryingEmbedder | 768 | 10,000 | 64 (then) | 1000 | 0.5124 | — | 0.90 | reference-only (not a gate) | `STATUS-perf-vector-quant.md` "Fixture-replacement evaluation" |

**Anchor (HITL-accepted for PR-3):** recall@10 = **0.937** (CI 0.913–0.957,
σ=0.0116) on the largest all-real-corpus haystack (N=7,667, K=192, bge-small +
mean-centering). The 0.90 floor HOLDS (R−2σ = 0.914). The earlier 0.828 was a
conservative-measurement artifact (exclude-after + body-string set GT); see
`dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2c-recall-rootcause.md` and
`ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md` §2 point 4. This is ANN/quantization
fidelity (GT = exact f32 top-10 over the SAME model), **not** IR relevance.
N=1M real recall is not measurable on this hardware (~166 h seed); recall
decreases slowly with N, so 0.937 @ N=7667 is an upper-ish bound for larger N.

## AC-019 — concurrent-mixed read tail (8 threads)

bound = max(baseline_p99 × 10, 150 ms).

| fixture | embedder | dim | N | threads | baseline p99 | stress p99 | bound | verdict | note / source |
