I found the structural risk in the smoke: the engine appends ordinary FTS5 matches after vector results, so the sentinel query must be non-matchable on the text side or the test can pass without exercising vector retrieval at all. I’m verifying SQLite’s tokenization of the quoted hyphenated sentinel directly in an in-memory FTS5 session so the finding rests on behavior, not guesswork.
