- **BLOCK**: `ac_013_vector_read_path_smoke` is not a genuine vector-path canary. The test searches for the literal sentinel body [`perf_gates.rs:752`](</home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:752>), but `search()` appends normal FTS5 hits after vector hits, and still does so when the vector stage returns nothing [`lib.rs:3205`](</home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3205>) [`lib.rs:3275`](</home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3275>). `compile_text_query()` wraps the raw query as a quoted FTS phrase [`fathomdb-query/src/lib.rs:12`](</home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-query/src/lib.rs:12>), and that quoted hyphenated sentinel is FTS-matchable. So if bit-KNN / rerank breaks and returns zero rows, the smoke can still pass via the text path alone. That directly undercuts the “per-push read-path guard” claim in [`perf_gates.rs:743`](</home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:743>) and [`0.7.2-PR-3-output.json:79`](</home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-3-output.json:79>).

